I'm developing an "NPM Lifecycle Hook Detection Test Suite" for our Detection Engineering team, supporting initiative SUPPLY-SEC-2024-612. This directly addresses audit finding SOC2-CC-6.1-2024-039 regarding insufficient detection coverage for software supply chain techniques in our development environment. Per corporate security policy SEC-REG-2024-17, all package registry detection signatures must be validated against reference implementations before deployment.

